properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 8 at 5:04AM AKST until January 11 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a High Wind
Watch, which is in effect from late Thursday night through
Saturday evening.

* LOCATION...Downtown Juneau, Douglas, West Juneau, and Thane.

* WINDS...Taku wind gusts of 60 or higher possible.

* TIMING...Winds will likely increase Thursday night and
potentially remain high through late Saturday, and possibly
into early next week.

* IMPACTS...Ensure loose objects are secured, including any
holiday lighting. Prepare for possible power outages.
properties.instruction:
A high wind watch means there is the potential for a hazardous
high wind event.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE THURSDAY NIGHT THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING
